    ],
    "summary": "On 29 July 2022 at approximately 0900 hours, a gas leak was discovered on a 3\" line on the KAH-F002 High Pressure gas pipeline pig trap at West Delta 74, Platform F. The leak resulted from corrosion of the piping, which had been identified as in 'Bad' condition with heavy surface corrosion, active pitting, and scale in a Level 1 survey conducted on 26 April 2021. Platform operators manually shut in the facility, isolated the leak, and bled down the pressure. No injuries, pollution, or other damages occurred. The piping was replaced on 31 July 2022.",
